Reporting to the Group Manager of Digital Technology, the Data and Power BI Analyst is responsible for maintaining, analysing, and visualising data across the organisation, ensuring data quality and accurate reporting. What We're All About.

It isn't often you get to be part of a tech company that, since 2016, has been innovating the data analytics market in ways no-one else can. Our technology started out in FinTech, helping tackle serious criminal activity. Now, its potential is virtually limitless. Working at Quantexa isn't just intellectually stimulating. We're a real team. Collaborating and constantly engineering better and better solutions. We're ambitious, we think things through and we're on a mission to discover just how far we can go. Nearly half of our colleagues come from an ethnic or religious minority background. We're made up of people from 47 nationalities who speak over 20 languages. As a diverse mix of individuals, we make one big unstoppable team.

If our incredible culture sounds like you, we'd love you to join us.



Our Big Data Graduate Programme is designed for you to develop your technical skill set, think creatively and be a real problem solver of major issues our clients are facing today. If you are someone who likes to think outside the box, holds a real passion for data and is open to new ideas, you'll find a Qmmunity that recognises your needs to be a creative innovator and embrace it. 🧬

You will work on big data projects where you will have exposure to data science, data engineering and DevOps methods, whilst learning to engage with both internal and external stakeholders. In a typical Quantexa project, you'll work with high volume data, helping our top clients solve business problems in financial crime, fraud and money laundering along with playing a huge part in helping our others solve complex terrorism cases, human trafficking, and even modern-day slavery. You'll be working closely with Data Scientists, Data Engineers, Business Analysts, Technical Leads, Project Managers and Solutions Architects, using entity resolution to generate networks and apply a scoring framework to identify risks. At Quantexa everyone is following the same goal of meeting our client's expectations and delivering a first-class service. 🥇



We want our graduates to learn the latest Big Data technologies and being the huge fans of functional programming that we are, your first 3 months will consist of going through our dedicated training academy. You'll have exposure to learning Scala, which is our primary language here at Quantexa, so you are confident and comfortable using our platform. Part of this exciting journey will also have you exposed to other tools such as Spark, Hadoop, Hive, Kubernetes, with our platform being hosted on Google cloud (GCP). You will learn how to create entities and networks and loading data using Elasticsearch in the Quantexa interface. You'll be required to generate a solution using our explorer in a world leading big data tool set. This training is heavily self-paced learning giving you the flexibility to add to the task and complete with set timings.

Following completion of the academy you will be working on multiple projects. You can expect to work with different lead experts who share their love of big data to deliver the best for our clients.












What makes you Q will help you to realize your full potential, flourish and enjoy what you do, while being recognized and rewarded with our broad range of benefits.

Job Title: Virtual Data Analyst/Virtual Data Entry Clerk

Virtual Data Analyst/Virtual Data Entry Clerk Clerk/Office will be responsible for analyzing and interpreting large datasets to provide valuable insights and recommendations to the business. They will work closely with cross-functional teams to gather and analyze data, develop reports, and provide customized solutions to help the organization gain a competitive edge.

Are you a seasoned Product Designer with a passion for crafting exceptional user experiences? Join a dynamic team in Sydney within the rapidly expanding PharmaTech sector, where your work will directly impact the future of digital healthcare solutions.



End-to-End Product (UX) Design: Take full ownership of the product lifecycle, from ideation through to planning, design, and delivery. You’ll lead the effort in consolidating two existing platforms into one seamless user experience.

Platform Enhancement: Work with business and engineering teams to improve platform features, ensuring a more user-friendly and visually appealing interface.

UX/UI Research: Conduct comprehensive user research, using both primary and secondary methods, to deeply understand user needs, preferences, and pain points. Translate these insights into actionable design solutions that are user-centred.

Prototyping & Wireframing: Develop detailed user flows, wireframes, prototypes, and mock-ups using tools like Figma. Continuously refine these designs based on user feedback and usability testing.

User Testing: Plan and conduct user testing sessions to validate design concepts, identify usability issues, and refine designs to optimise the user experience.

Product Management: Maintain and operate the product backlog and sprints, ensuring that all design solutions align with broader business/product objectives and technical constraints.

Team Collaboration: Collaborate with all stakeholders to ensure design solutions meet user needs and business goals.

Design System Management: Maintain and evolve the design system to ensure consistency across all touchpoints of the platform, delivering a unified user experience.

Analytics Integration: Work with the data team to design and integrate a robust analytics product into the platform, providing users with clear and actionable insights.

Feedback: Continuously incorporate customer feedback, usage metrics, and usability findings into your designs to enhance the overall user experience.



Proven Expertise: You have a demonstrated ability to manage the full lifecycle of digital products, particularly within an Agile environment, with experience in maintaining and operating product backlogs and sprints. Ideal candidates will have honed their craft on digital products at the startup and/or scaleup level, and in addition to Product Design also have solid Product Management expertise.

Product Design Evangelist: Your portfolio reflects your expertise as a Product (UX/UI) Designer, with a strong track record of creating user-centred designs that are both functional and visually compelling.

Tool Proficiency: You are proficient in design and prototyping tools such as Sketch and Figma, with a basic understanding of HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript that enhances your collaboration with development teams.

Attention to Detail: You possess a keen eye for aesthetics and a strong attention to detail, ensuring your designs are polished and meet high standards of quality.

Effective Communicator: You have excellent communication skills, enabling you to articulate your ideas clearly and collaborate effectively with different stakeholders. You thrive in a team-oriented environment and are passionate about technology and innovation.

Continuous Learner: You are driven by a desire to continuously improve your skills and stay updated with the latest design trends and technologies. Your approach to problem-solving is both analytical and creative.
